President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Deborah A. P. Hersman is nominated for Chairman of the National Transportation Safety Board. She has served on the Board since 2004 and has been involved in numerous transportation accidents. Thomas C. Krajeski is nominated for Ambassador to the Kingdom of Bahrain. He has been a career member of the Foreign Service since 1979 and has served in various diplomatic roles. Robert A. Mandell is nominated for Ambassador to Luxembourg. He is currently the Chairman and CEO of a commercial real estate venture in Florida. Hal Simpson is appointed as the United States Representative to the Rio Grande Compact Commission. He has a background in water resources management.